1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:04,963
[LIAM] <i>We're making a dish using</i>
<i>whatever ingredients are here.</i>

2
00:00:05,046 --> 00:00:08,466
<i>The fastest and tastiest food we can make</i>
<i>that will be enough for a lot of people.</i>

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,385
<i>This is what's going to save us.</i>

4
00:00:10,468 --> 00:00:13,304
<i>Doc, I need you to get</i>
<i>the most important ingredient.</i>

5
00:00:14,597 --> 00:00:16,141
[GOON] <i>How far are we from our target?</i>

6
00:00:16,224 --> 00:00:17,851
[MIKE] <i>More or less three meters left.</i>

7
00:00:17,934 --> 00:00:20,228
<i>We're about to reach the old sewage pipe.</i>

8
00:00:20,311 --> 00:00:21,646
<i>Once you break through that,</i>

9
00:00:21,730 --> 00:00:24,023
<i>you'll have an exit path</i>
<i>out of this hospital.</i>

10
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:25,942
[DADO] <i>They tried to play us.</i>

11
00:00:26,025 --> 00:00:27,068
<i>- Kneel down!</i>
- [GRUNTS]

12
00:00:27,152 --> 00:00:28,570
<i>Olsen! My son!</i>

13
00:00:28,653 --> 00:00:29,529
<i>He's your son?</i>

14
00:00:31,573 --> 00:00:33,450
- [MAN 1] <i>Hey! What's that?</i>
- [MAN 2] <i>Drop it!</i>

15
00:00:33,533 --> 00:00:34,534
<i>Liam?</i>

16
00:00:34,617 --> 00:00:36,745
- [THWACKS]
- [GRUNTS]

17
00:00:36,828 --> 00:00:38,663
<i>Where are your companions?</i>

18
00:00:38,747 --> 00:00:40,415
<i>They're hiding in the commissary.</i>

19
00:00:41,082 --> 00:00:41,958
<i>Check it out.</i>

20
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:44,043
<i>If your son is fooling me,</i>

21
00:00:44,127 --> 00:00:46,629
<i>he'll come back to you as a corpse.</i>

22
00:00:47,630 --> 00:00:48,631
[DADO] <i>Hurry up.</i>

23
00:00:49,174 --> 00:00:53,303
<i>Pull a fast one on me again,</i>
<i>and I'll shoot you myself.</i>

24
00:00:54,846 --> 00:00:56,181
<i>I hope this works.</i>

25
00:01:04,731 --> 00:01:07,692
<i>When we were in the staff house,</i>

26
00:01:08,443 --> 00:01:10,111
<i>Papa's urn shattered.</i>

27
00:01:10,195 --> 00:01:12,238
<i>- I didn't find--</i>
<i>- Liam! </i>[OLSEN GROANS]

28
00:01:12,322 --> 00:01:13,531
<i>I dropped Papa!</i>

29
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:15,992
<i>Why was it filled with sand?</i>

30
00:01:16,076 --> 00:01:18,703
<i>It doesn't matter, son.</i>

31
00:01:18,787 --> 00:01:22,415
<i>All you need to know is that</i>
<i>he's a good-for-nothing man.</i>

32
00:01:22,499 --> 00:01:25,126
<i>My father… isn't dead?</i>

33
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:27,378
<i>Why don't you tell him?</i>

34
00:01:29,005 --> 00:01:32,759
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

35
00:01:34,761 --> 00:01:37,764
This is none of your business.

36
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:39,432
Who the heck is he?

37
00:01:39,516 --> 00:01:42,310
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

38
00:01:42,393 --> 00:01:43,728
Why don't you tell him?

39
00:01:44,604 --> 00:01:46,815
It's none of your business!

40
00:01:46,898 --> 00:01:48,066
[CHUCKLES]

41
00:01:48,149 --> 00:01:51,111
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

42
00:01:52,445 --> 00:01:55,156
Since your mother
doesn't want to introduce me,

43
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:57,742
I'll just introduce myself.

44
00:01:59,619 --> 00:02:02,288
My name is Homer Sebastian.

45
00:02:03,081 --> 00:02:05,291
I was in a relationship
with your mother in the past.

46
00:02:06,334 --> 00:02:08,253
We even lived together.

47
00:02:08,336 --> 00:02:09,462
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

48
00:02:09,546 --> 00:02:13,925
Now, if you're wondering
who your father is…

49
00:02:16,386 --> 00:02:19,055
I'm also wondering, Olsen,

50
00:02:20,014 --> 00:02:21,975
if you are my son.

51
00:02:22,058 --> 00:02:24,144
Olsen is not your son!

52
00:02:24,227 --> 00:02:25,478
He is not your son!

53
00:02:26,187 --> 00:02:27,021
[WENDY WHIMPERS]

54
00:02:27,105 --> 00:02:28,314
[HOMER] Wendy.

55
00:02:29,983 --> 00:02:31,776
This is your chance.

56
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:35,405
If you say that Olsen is my son,

57
00:02:35,488 --> 00:02:37,824
I might show the two of you some mercy.

58
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:42,537
Remember, someone here wants you dead.

59
00:02:42,620 --> 00:02:45,290
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

60
00:02:45,373 --> 00:02:47,375
Do you remember what they told Jacinto?

61
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:50,712
No one should get hurt,

62
00:02:50,795 --> 00:02:52,672
except for you.

63
00:02:54,716 --> 00:02:56,968
Now, whoever that person is,

64
00:02:57,051 --> 00:03:01,389
they want your mother dead.

65
00:03:02,098 --> 00:03:03,725
Don't you want my protection?

66
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:06,102
I don't need you.

67
00:03:06,185 --> 00:03:07,103
[HOMER SCOFFS]

68
00:03:07,186 --> 00:03:10,440
But back then, you needed me
when you had nowhere else to go

69
00:03:10,523 --> 00:03:12,233
because you were so heartbroken

70
00:03:12,317 --> 00:03:14,986
by whoever you were in
a relationship with at the resort.

71
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:17,864
Am I right, huh?

72
00:03:17,947 --> 00:03:19,616
Am I right?

73
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:23,369
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

74
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:25,622
[HOMER] Wendy… Aww.

75
00:03:25,705 --> 00:03:27,040
Don't cry.

76
00:03:27,123 --> 00:03:29,500
Didn't you miss me, Wendy? Hmm?

77
00:03:30,084 --> 00:03:31,669
[OLSEN] Don't touch her!

78
00:03:31,753 --> 00:03:34,631
- [HOMER CHUCKLING]
- Don't touch her.

79
00:03:34,714 --> 00:03:37,133
Mm-hmm. Okay, okay.

80
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:39,052
Okay, I won't touch her again.

81
00:03:39,719 --> 00:03:41,346
Now,

82
00:03:41,429 --> 00:03:45,058
if you're telling the truth
that Olsen isn't my son,

83
00:03:45,141 --> 00:03:49,604
then I can just take my anger out on him.

84
00:03:49,687 --> 00:03:50,688
Right?

85
00:03:50,772 --> 00:03:51,981
Come here!

86
00:03:52,065 --> 00:03:53,483
[WENDY WHIMPERS] No! Olsen!

87
00:03:55,151 --> 00:03:56,236
[WENDY] No!

88
00:03:56,319 --> 00:03:57,862
Where are you taking him?

89
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:03,243
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

90
00:04:10,875 --> 00:04:17,799
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

91
00:04:46,661 --> 00:04:48,162
No!

92
00:04:48,246 --> 00:04:51,207
No, no, no. Don't interfere. Step aside.

93
00:04:51,291 --> 00:04:52,333
Just stay there!

94
00:04:52,417 --> 00:04:54,544
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

95
00:04:54,627 --> 00:04:55,962
[LUCAS] Move back!

96
00:04:56,838 --> 00:04:59,048
- Don't be stubborn, okay?
- [WENDY WHIMPERS]

97
00:05:02,468 --> 00:05:03,594
[LUCAS] Brother.

98
00:05:03,678 --> 00:05:05,054
Go beat him up.

99
00:05:06,681 --> 00:05:11,060
He was one of the reasons
why our mission on the island failed.

100
00:05:13,688 --> 00:05:16,190
So, what are we waiting for?

101
00:05:18,318 --> 00:05:20,862
Let's party. Fight!

102
00:05:20,945 --> 00:05:24,615
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

103
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:33,041
[DADO] Get in! Hurry!

104
00:05:33,124 --> 00:05:34,125
Stop what you're doing.

105
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:37,503
- [FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]
- All of you, line up now!

106
00:05:37,587 --> 00:05:38,504
[CONRAD] Move it!

107
00:05:39,464 --> 00:05:40,465
[DADO] Conrad.

108
00:05:40,548 --> 00:05:41,924
Search them.

109
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:43,134
Turn around. Face the wall.

110
00:05:43,217 --> 00:05:45,803
- I said turn around.
- [DADO] Nobody move.

111
00:05:45,887 --> 00:05:49,265
I'm glad you were telling the truth, Liam.

112
00:05:49,348 --> 00:05:51,517
I thought you were going
to trick me again.

113
00:05:53,269 --> 00:05:54,479
All clear?

114
00:05:54,562 --> 00:05:57,732
Who will bring these upstairs?

115
00:05:57,815 --> 00:06:00,443
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

116
00:06:00,526 --> 00:06:02,278
Hurry up!

117
00:06:03,654 --> 00:06:04,697
You.

118
00:06:05,990 --> 00:06:07,116
Move it.

119
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:13,414
Were you the one who cooked that?

120
00:06:13,498 --> 00:06:14,832
Boss, this looks good.

121
00:06:18,127 --> 00:06:19,670
Wait, go back there.

122
00:06:20,296 --> 00:06:21,631
Move it. Hurry up.

123
00:06:23,466 --> 00:06:24,717
Give us some plates.

124
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:26,969
- Get us plates! Hurry!
- [GASPS]

125
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:31,808
Faster.

126
00:06:33,351 --> 00:06:35,353
- Where will I sit?
- [HAPPY] Oh, wait.

127
00:06:39,357 --> 00:06:40,858
Go back there.

128
00:06:40,942 --> 00:06:41,984
Move it. Hurry up.

129
00:06:43,778 --> 00:06:45,863
Nobody move. Hmm?

130
00:06:45,947 --> 00:06:49,283
Don't even think of pulling a stunt.

131
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:53,496
Let's try this.

132
00:06:53,579 --> 00:06:58,709
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

133
00:06:59,377 --> 00:07:00,586
[DADO EXHALES SHARPLY]

134
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:04,298
Keep an eye on them, okay?

135
00:07:05,883 --> 00:07:10,471
[UTENSILS CLINKING]

136
00:07:10,555 --> 00:07:11,806
I'm hungry.

137
00:07:14,851 --> 00:07:15,810
[DADO] Mm.

138
00:07:15,893 --> 00:07:18,146
[MUNCHING]

139
00:07:18,729 --> 00:07:20,231
This is so good. Who made this?

140
00:07:22,233 --> 00:07:23,359
Huh?

141
00:07:25,653 --> 00:07:28,030
If you don't want to answer, that's fine.

142
00:07:28,114 --> 00:07:29,615
[CONRAD] Is there anything to drink?

143
00:07:30,283 --> 00:07:35,413
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

144
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,668
- [SHOVELS SCRAPING]
- [MAN GRUNTS]

145
00:07:40,751 --> 00:07:42,795
[MIKE] Hey! Wait, hold on!

146
00:07:44,005 --> 00:07:46,007
Be careful not to hit the water pipe,

147
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:48,092
or we'll get flooded here.

148
00:07:49,135 --> 00:07:51,554
[MIKE] Carry on. But please be careful.

149
00:07:51,637 --> 00:07:55,183
- [MEN GRUNTING]
- [SHOVELS SCRAPING]

150
00:08:00,062 --> 00:08:06,736
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

151
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:29,509
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

152
00:08:32,136 --> 00:08:36,432
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

153
00:08:36,516 --> 00:08:37,600
[GUN COCKS]

154
00:08:37,683 --> 00:08:38,976
- Liam!
- [LIAM HUFFS]

155
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,645
What are you doing?

156
00:08:43,814 --> 00:08:45,900
He's going to kill us once they wake up!

157
00:08:45,983 --> 00:08:47,944
We are not murderers.

158
00:08:48,027 --> 00:08:51,155
This guy has killed a lot of people!

159
00:08:51,948 --> 00:08:53,741
If you do that,

160
00:08:53,824 --> 00:08:55,743
you won't be any different from them.

161
00:08:56,994 --> 00:08:58,955
I know you want to get even with them,

162
00:08:59,038 --> 00:09:00,831
but this isn't the right way.

163
00:09:06,337 --> 00:09:11,509
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

164
00:09:11,592 --> 00:09:13,719
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

165
00:09:13,803 --> 00:09:15,388
Get his earpiece.

166
00:09:22,687 --> 00:09:24,188
This way, we can hear their plans.

167
00:09:27,149 --> 00:09:28,276
Tie them up.

168
00:09:28,359 --> 00:09:29,193
Is there a rope?

169
00:09:29,277 --> 00:09:30,903
[JOY] Let's look for a rope.

170
00:09:31,487 --> 00:09:32,822
- Come on.
- Let's go.

171
00:09:32,905 --> 00:09:39,203
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [BREATHING HEAVILY, GRUNTING]

172
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:46,836
- Who are we going to bet on?
- [WENDY WHIMPERING]

173
00:09:47,712 --> 00:09:49,672
Huh? You!

174
00:09:49,755 --> 00:09:52,174
Who are you going to bet on? Hmm?

175
00:09:52,258 --> 00:09:53,551
You!

176
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,263
My older brother Homer

177
00:09:58,931 --> 00:10:00,933
or the young security officer?

178
00:10:01,726 --> 00:10:03,561
Do you even have to ask?

179
00:10:03,644 --> 00:10:05,187
[LUCAS CHUCKLING]

180
00:10:05,271 --> 00:10:06,397
All right, kid.

181
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:11,694
If I lose, I will let your mother go.

182
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:13,195
[UNEASY MUSIC PLAYING]

183
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:15,031
[HOMER] But

184
00:10:15,114 --> 00:10:17,283
if I beat you,

185
00:10:17,366 --> 00:10:19,619
I'll push your mother off the building!

186
00:10:21,871 --> 00:10:23,664
[SOBS]

187
00:10:31,130 --> 00:10:32,340
I won't fight.

188
00:10:32,423 --> 00:10:34,425
There's no backing out now, boy.

189
00:10:39,597 --> 00:10:41,057
[SOFTLY] Guys, I've got a plan.

190
00:10:41,974 --> 00:10:43,184
[WHISPERS] What are you thinking?

191
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:46,145
What are we supposed to look for?

192
00:10:46,228 --> 00:10:47,813
These things attached to us…

193
00:10:48,606 --> 00:10:51,233
They're like what we use in silent raves.

194
00:10:52,193 --> 00:10:54,403
Same idea, different purpose.

195
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:57,073
My gosh, I get it now.

196
00:10:57,156 --> 00:11:00,117
Those devices they use
at those parties, right?

197
00:11:00,201 --> 00:11:01,744
[FIN] Wait, wait, wait.

198
00:11:01,827 --> 00:11:03,996
People are killing each other,
and you're talking parties?

199
00:11:04,080 --> 00:11:05,247
[MACKY] No, man.

200
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:09,126
This is about transmitters and receivers.

201
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:15,257
In silent raves,
all the headphones people wear,

202
00:11:15,341 --> 00:11:20,930
they have receivers connected
to one device the DJ holds.

203
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:22,515
That's the transmitter.

204
00:11:22,598 --> 00:11:26,435
When you leave the club…
same concept, right?

205
00:11:26,519 --> 00:11:28,604
- [MACKY] Yes. That's right.
- Bluetooth, but with a range.

206
00:11:28,687 --> 00:11:31,023
These are receivers.

207
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:35,861
So if we find the transmitter,
we can deactivate the bombs.

208
00:11:37,113 --> 00:11:38,322
[EDUARDO HUFFS]

209
00:11:38,406 --> 00:11:41,242
I guess all that partying
paid off after all.

210
00:11:41,325 --> 00:11:43,994
[MACKY CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
Well, yeah. Maybe you're right.

211
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:47,456
Let's find the transmitter
once they make their move.

212
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:48,958
Yes, sir.

213
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:54,338
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

214
00:11:56,298 --> 00:12:00,845
[MUSIC BECOMES UNEASY]

215
00:12:00,928 --> 00:12:02,847
[GRUNTS]

216
00:12:02,930 --> 00:12:05,516
These guys will stay knocked out
till later, right, Doc?

217
00:12:05,599 --> 00:12:11,147
[UNEASY MUSIC CONTINUES]

218
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:14,733
And here we were planning
to feed all the demons.

219
00:12:14,817 --> 00:12:15,693
[JOY SCOFFS]

220
00:12:15,776 --> 00:12:19,447
Yeah. These demons are starving.

221
00:12:21,949 --> 00:12:25,536
Liam, they'll definitely
look for these two.

222
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:27,288
What do we do?

223
00:12:29,039 --> 00:12:33,752
We need to find an exit
so I can at least get you out.

224
00:12:33,836 --> 00:12:36,755
[LOW, SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

225
00:12:36,839 --> 00:12:38,007
Just us?

226
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:43,304
Luna, you know I can't leave
Mama and Papa behind.

227
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:48,225
Sir Liam, how do we get out?

228
00:12:48,309 --> 00:12:51,187
Every entrance and exit
has a bomb attached.

229
00:12:54,273 --> 00:12:59,153
Don't worry. We'll find that doctor.

230
00:12:59,236 --> 00:13:05,659
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

231
00:13:13,501 --> 00:13:14,960
[LENI] Pa…

232
00:13:17,630 --> 00:13:18,964
Pa.

233
00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:21,884
- [EMIL] Leni…
- Pa.

234
00:13:21,967 --> 00:13:23,344
You're safe, Pa.

235
00:13:23,427 --> 00:13:24,970
How are you, dear?

236
00:13:25,679 --> 00:13:30,142
I'm begging you to stop this.

237
00:13:31,644 --> 00:13:33,771
Let's go home, Pa. Please.

238
00:13:34,855 --> 00:13:38,776
Yes, dear. We'll be leaving soon.

239
00:13:39,401 --> 00:13:41,529
I already have our millions.

240
00:13:42,655 --> 00:13:47,535
And the passage out of the hospital
is almost finished.

241
00:13:49,703 --> 00:13:51,580
You've got to get better, dear.

242
00:13:53,457 --> 00:13:57,127
Soon, we'll be together again
with your sister Ayen.

243
00:13:57,211 --> 00:14:01,215
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

244
00:14:01,298 --> 00:14:02,424
[SMOOCHES]

245
00:14:02,508 --> 00:14:09,515
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

246
00:14:23,529 --> 00:14:26,156
It'll be risky to break the glass, sir.

247
00:14:26,240 --> 00:14:30,077
Any movement could trigger the bomb.

248
00:14:32,079 --> 00:14:34,081
There must be another way.

249
00:14:34,164 --> 00:14:37,251
Maybe there's an entry or exit
we're not seeing.

250
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:40,796
I got it.

251
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:46,677
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

252
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:52,600
Fight!

253
00:14:57,313 --> 00:15:02,985
[OMINOUS MUSIC BUILDS]

254
00:15:03,068 --> 00:15:04,486
[GRUNTS]

255
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:06,697
[LUCAS] Whoo!

256
00:15:06,780 --> 00:15:08,365
Go, Homer!

257
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:10,242
[MEN LAUGHING]

258
00:15:10,326 --> 00:15:12,453
- [HOMER] Come on, boy!
- [LUCAS LAUGHING]

259
00:15:12,536 --> 00:15:14,622
Well? You think you can handle it, boy?

260
00:15:14,705 --> 00:15:21,003
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

261
00:15:26,508 --> 00:15:29,595
[BOTH GRUNTING]

262
00:15:29,678 --> 00:15:31,972
- Oh, he can fight.
- Come on.

263
00:15:32,056 --> 00:15:33,515
- [LUCAS] Impressive!
- [MAN] Nice!

264
00:15:33,599 --> 00:15:38,646
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

265
00:15:40,397 --> 00:15:42,024
[HOMER GRUNTS IN DISTANCE]

266
00:15:42,107 --> 00:15:43,525
Wait. Hold on.

267
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:46,695
Take that side.

268
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:48,864
I'll take this side.

269
00:15:49,615 --> 00:15:54,870
- [TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]
- [RITA BREATHING SHAKILY]

270
00:15:58,374 --> 00:15:59,792
[MAN] Go get him!

271
00:15:59,875 --> 00:16:00,834
[IVAN BREATHES SHARPLY]

272
00:16:00,918 --> 00:16:04,338
There's a way here to the veranda,
but we'll need to jump.

273
00:16:04,421 --> 00:16:05,339
"Jump?"

274
00:16:05,422 --> 00:16:08,509
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

275
00:16:08,592 --> 00:16:09,593
Come on! Let's go!

276
00:16:12,721 --> 00:16:14,098
[MACKY WHISPERS] Hey, wait.

277
00:16:14,181 --> 00:16:16,058
- Shh. Keep it down.
- [RITA] Sorry, sorry, sorry.

278
00:16:16,141 --> 00:16:18,143
- Be careful. Careful.
- Sorry, sorry.

279
00:16:19,061 --> 00:16:21,605
[HOMER, OLSEN GRUNTING IN DISTANCE]

280
00:16:21,689 --> 00:16:28,696
[MEN LAUGHING, CHEERING]

281
00:16:29,947 --> 00:16:30,906
[MAN] Hit him!

282
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:36,370
[MEN CLAMORING
INDISTINCTLY IN DISTANCE]

283
00:16:36,453 --> 00:16:38,872
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

284
00:16:38,956 --> 00:16:39,873
[BREATHES SHARPLY]

285
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:43,794
- [MAN] Come on! Go for it!
- [LUCAS LAUGHING]

286
00:16:44,503 --> 00:16:47,715
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

287
00:16:47,798 --> 00:16:48,924
[WHISPERS] Rita.

288
00:16:50,092 --> 00:16:51,844
I found the transmitter.

289
00:16:51,927 --> 00:16:55,347
[RITA BREATHES SHAKILY]

290
00:16:57,808 --> 00:17:02,730
- [SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [TRANSMITTER BEEPING]

291
00:17:02,813 --> 00:17:04,314
[HOMER, OLSEN GRUNTING IN DISTANCE]

292
00:17:04,398 --> 00:17:05,315
[MACKY BREATHES SHARPLY]

293
00:17:05,399 --> 00:17:08,610
[HOMER, OLSEN GRUNTING IN DISTANCE]

294
00:17:08,694 --> 00:17:10,696
- [MACKY CHUCKLES]
- [RITA BREATHING SHAKILY]

295
00:17:10,779 --> 00:17:12,823
[TRANSMITTER BEEPING]

296
00:17:14,241 --> 00:17:15,159
Oops.

297
00:17:15,242 --> 00:17:16,326
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

298
00:17:16,410 --> 00:17:18,162
Wait. Hold on.

299
00:17:18,245 --> 00:17:19,872
[LIAM BREATHING HEAVILY]

300
00:17:19,955 --> 00:17:20,873
Liam!

301
00:17:20,956 --> 00:17:23,083
[BOMB TICKING]

302
00:17:23,167 --> 00:17:24,835
Are there other exits, Doc?

303
00:17:24,918 --> 00:17:26,503
[BOMB TICKING]

304
00:17:30,215 --> 00:17:36,263
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

305
00:17:36,346 --> 00:17:37,806
- Oh, watch out.
- Look at that.

306
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:39,349
[LUCAS LAUGHING]

307
00:17:41,727 --> 00:17:45,481
- [GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

308
00:17:50,778 --> 00:17:51,653
[LUCAS] Hey!

309
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:52,821
[OLSEN GRUNTS]

310
00:17:53,614 --> 00:17:56,283
- Is it bleeding? I feel it.
- Yes, bro.

311
00:17:56,366 --> 00:17:58,118
[OLSEN] You like that?

312
00:17:58,202 --> 00:17:59,536
- Huh?
- Come on.

313
00:17:59,620 --> 00:18:01,330
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

314
00:18:01,413 --> 00:18:03,665
- [GRUNTS]
- [LUCAS] Whoo!

315
00:18:03,749 --> 00:18:06,043
- [GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

316
00:18:06,126 --> 00:18:08,587
[ONLOOKERS CHEERING
AND JEERING]

317
00:18:08,670 --> 00:18:12,049
- [MEN CLAMORING INDISTINCTLY]
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

318
00:18:12,132 --> 00:18:14,760
- [GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

319
00:18:14,843 --> 00:18:16,720
- [HOMER GRUNTS]
- [LUCAS] Take that!

320
00:18:16,804 --> 00:18:19,807
- [MUSIC BECOMES MOROSE]
- [CRYING]

321
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:20,974
[HOMER] Come on!

322
00:18:21,058 --> 00:18:23,393
- [MAN 1] Come on!
- [HOMER] Fight, boy!

323
00:18:23,477 --> 00:18:25,813
- [MAN 1 LAUGHS] Fight!
- [MAN 2] Go for it!

324
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:27,898
[HOMER GRUNTS]

325
00:18:29,525 --> 00:18:31,568
- [GRUNTS]
- [LUCAS LAUGHS]

326
00:18:31,652 --> 00:18:34,655
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

327
00:18:34,738 --> 00:18:36,031
[OLSEN GROANS]

328
00:18:36,865 --> 00:18:38,158
- [GRUNTS]
- [THUDS]

329
00:18:38,242 --> 00:18:42,204
- [GRUNTING]
- [BLOWS LANDING]

330
00:18:43,747 --> 00:18:44,748
[LUCAS] Brother!

331
00:18:44,832 --> 00:18:46,500
- Fight!
- Stand up!

332
00:18:46,583 --> 00:18:49,920
- [LUCAS GRUNTS] Brother! Stand up!
- [WENDY CRYING]

333
00:18:50,003 --> 00:18:52,548
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WENDY CRYING] Enough.

334
00:18:52,631 --> 00:18:53,590
[GUN CLICKS]

335
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:56,677
Go ahead!

336
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,512
- [OLSEN] Ma, don't.
- [WENDY] Stop it!

337
00:18:58,595 --> 00:19:00,389
- [OLSEN] Stop!
- [WENDY] That's enough!

338
00:19:00,472 --> 00:19:01,515
[HOMER] I dare you!

339
00:19:02,432 --> 00:19:05,435
Do you want me to make your injury worse?!
Move back!

340
00:19:05,519 --> 00:19:07,729
- [TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [WENDY CRYING]

341
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:09,648
Please, that's enough.

342
00:19:10,524 --> 00:19:11,942
[WENDY] Homer, please stop.

343
00:19:12,025 --> 00:19:12,901
It's over.

344
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:15,237
Oh, is that so?!

345
00:19:15,320 --> 00:19:17,072
- Stop it!
- You lost!

346
00:19:17,156 --> 00:19:20,200
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

347
00:19:20,284 --> 00:19:21,869
[SCREAMS]

348
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,835
<i>I know what kind of bombs they planted.</i>

349
00:19:29,918 --> 00:19:31,253
<i>Military-type IED.</i>

350
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:32,838
<i>We can't move it. It might explode.</i>

351
00:19:32,921 --> 00:19:34,214
<i>Do you know how to disarm bombs?</i>

352
00:19:34,298 --> 00:19:37,759
<i>I'll teach you how to disarm a bomb.</i>
<i>Listen to everything I say.</i>

353
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:38,844
[BLOWS LANDING]

354
00:19:38,927 --> 00:19:41,221
<i>- Homer, please stop!</i>
<i>- It's over.</i>

355
00:19:41,305 --> 00:19:43,557
<i>Oh, is that so?!</i>

356
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:46,435
<i>- Stop it!</i>
<i>- You lost!</i>

357
00:19:46,518 --> 00:19:51,481
<i>I really don't understand</i>
<i>why you had to meddle.</i>

358
00:19:51,565 --> 00:19:54,484
<i>They were going to kill Olsen.</i>

359
00:19:54,568 --> 00:19:56,195
<i>Olsen is not your son.</i>

360
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:58,947
<i>He's probably the son of that monster.</i>

361
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:00,741
<i>I won't just abandon him.</i>

362
00:20:00,824 --> 00:20:02,451
<i>Do you still love Wendy?</i>

363
00:20:03,744 --> 00:20:06,997
<i>Did you know that she</i>
<i>and Magnus Roja had an affair?</i>

364
00:20:07,456 --> 00:20:11,210
<i>Magnus might be the reason</i>
<i>Wendy left the resort.</i>

365
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:12,794
<i>Is he really my father?</i>

366
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:15,964
<i>Tell me the truth, Ma.</i>

367
00:20:18,592 --> 00:20:19,718
<i>I'm ready.</i>

368
00:20:19,801 --> 00:20:20,928
[AREZA] <i>Okay.</i>

369
00:20:21,011 --> 00:20:23,263
<i>Find the latch</i>
<i>at the side of the doorframe.</i>

370
00:20:23,347 --> 00:20:24,890
<i>Be careful, Liam.</i>

371
00:20:24,973 --> 00:20:26,934
[LIAM] <i>There's a small control board</i>

372
00:20:27,017 --> 00:20:29,269
<i>and a terminal block</i>
<i>numbered one to three.</i>

373
00:20:29,353 --> 00:20:30,562
<i>They share a common ground.</i>

374
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:32,606
<i>I don't see a wireless receiver.</i>

375
00:20:32,689 --> 00:20:34,524
<i>It might be timer-based</i>
<i>or contact-triggered.</i>

376
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:37,110
[AREZA] <i>It only passes through</i>
<i>terminal number three.</i>

377
00:20:37,194 --> 00:20:41,323
<i>The rest are decoy or secondary lines.</i>

378
00:20:41,406 --> 00:20:42,908
<i>Don't touch lines one and two.</i>

379
00:20:42,991 --> 00:20:45,202
<i>They're not part of the active circuit.</i>

380
00:20:45,285 --> 00:20:48,914
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

381
00:20:53,460 --> 00:20:58,840
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]
